        body: "These are two different ways to measure a process:<br><br>\ud83d\udce6 <strong>Throughput</strong> = how many units come out per hour (set by the bottleneck). Think: \"How many pizzas does the restaurant serve per hour?\"<br><br>\u23f1\ufe0f <strong>Flow Time</strong> = how long ONE unit takes from start to finish. Think: \"How long does MY pizza take from ordering to eating?\"<br><br>A restaurant can have high throughput (100 pizzas/hour) but long flow time (45 min per pizza) if there's lots of work-in-progress. Little's Law connects them."
