      icon: "\uD83D\uDCCB",
      body: "Contracts that help align retailer incentives with the supply chain optimum:<br><br>&bull; <strong>Buyback contracts:</strong> Manufacturer buys back unsold units at an agreed price &rarr; lowers retailer's C<sub>o</sub> &rarr; higher CR &rarr; higher Q*<br>&bull; <strong>Revenue sharing:</strong> Retailer pays lower wholesale price but shares a fraction of revenue with manufacturer<br>&bull; <strong>Quantity discounts:</strong> Lower per-unit price for larger orders<br><br>All these mechanisms \"share the risk\" of unsold inventory, encouraging the retailer to order closer to the integrated SC optimum."
